answers.a: E141 is the EU food additive code for copper complexes of chlorophylls and chlorophyllins, a green coloring; it doesn’t refer to a person or brand.

answers.q: in pulsepoint what to eh e141 m141 and ut41 numbers sigify
answers.a: As E-numbers, E141 denotes copper complexes of chlorophylls/chlorophyllins (a green food color); the other strings you mention aren’t recognized EU food additive codes.

answers.q: what does a e141/4x22rtr solas fit
answers.a: That SOLAS propeller code is unrelated to food additives; on food labels, E141 means the green color copper complexes of chlorophylls/chlorophyllins.

answers.q: what does a e141/4x22rtr solas prop fit
answers.a: It’s not related to E-numbers; E141 on foods refers to copper complexes of chlorophylls/chlorophyllins used as a green color.

E141 means copper complexes of chlorophylls and chlorophyllins, a green food color derived from plant chlorophyll (natural or semi‑synthetic). It includes E141(i) oil‑soluble chlorophyll complexes and E141(ii) water‑soluble chlorophyllin complexes.
